But it never did let up on the pressure . 
Until recently , a farmer with no heir had to will the state his land to collect his pension . 
The pension 's size still depends on how much produce he sells the state . 
Yet the state alone sells seeds and machines . 
A private farmer in Poland is free to buy and sell land , hire help , decide what to grow and how to grow it . 
He is free to invest in chickens , and to fail for lack of chicken wire . 
`` I 'm on my own land , '' Mr. Pyszkiewicz says . 
By starving the peasant , the Communists have starved Poland . 
Villages like Zalubice exist in a desert of poor schools and few doctors . 
Farm income is 15 % below the average . 
Farm income is 15 % below the average . The young leave , especially girls who wo n't milk cows by hand . 
